WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:09.080
Dominoes, Quick Starter, The Skateboarder, by Christine Lindop.

00:09.080 --> 00:11.120
CHAPTER I

00:11.120 --> 00:28.840
No Skateboard

00:28.840 --> 00:34.200
After Hannah's house, there's a new skate park.

00:34.200 --> 00:43.520
A lot of young people in the town go there after school with their skateboards.

00:43.520 --> 00:50.120
These days, Hannah often goes there with her cousin, Justin.

00:50.120 --> 00:54.320
Justin goes to school with her.

00:54.320 --> 01:00.440
Hannah doesn't like school very much, or getting up early.

01:00.440 --> 01:08.880
She's always late, and she doesn't have many friends.

01:08.880 --> 01:16.920
But with the new skate park, she's suddenly very interested in skateboarding.

01:16.920 --> 01:24.240
The only thing is, Hannah has no skateboard.

01:24.240 --> 01:28.200
Sometimes, Justin asks Hannah,

01:28.200 --> 01:33.080
Hey, do you want to get on my skateboard?

01:33.080 --> 01:40.480
So she does, but not for long.

01:40.480 --> 01:45.920
She doesn't want to fall off in front of everybody.

01:45.920 --> 01:52.160
So usually, she watches the skateboarders.

01:52.160 --> 01:55.160
Owen is 15.

01:55.160 --> 01:58.080
He's a good skateboarder.

01:58.080 --> 02:04.560
He can do a lot of tricks.

02:04.560 --> 02:08.440
I love Owen's skateboarding.

02:08.440 --> 02:10.040
Hannah thinks.

02:10.040 --> 02:15.880
I want to jump and do tricks, too.

02:15.880 --> 02:19.880
Why don't you have a skateboard, Hannah?

02:19.880 --> 02:21.880
Justin asks her.

02:21.880 --> 02:24.520
That's a new thing for me.

02:24.520 --> 02:26.320
Skateboarding.

02:26.320 --> 02:28.600
Hannah answers.

02:28.600 --> 02:30.640
Then she thinks.

02:30.640 --> 02:33.280
My birthday's coming.

02:33.280 --> 02:50.920
Maybe I can talk to Mom and Dad.

02:50.920 --> 02:52.720
After two.

02:52.720 --> 02:54.360
Good grades.

02:54.360 --> 03:12.560
Better presents.

03:12.560 --> 03:18.520
On Hannah's birthday morning, she opens her presents.

03:18.520 --> 03:23.960
There's a big present from her mother and father.

03:23.960 --> 03:28.520
Hannah opens it first, excitedly.

03:28.520 --> 03:31.880
Wow.

03:31.880 --> 03:33.080
She cries.

03:33.080 --> 03:35.080
A skateboard.

03:35.080 --> 03:36.240
Thanks.

03:36.240 --> 03:42.160
Well, your school grades are good, Hannah.

03:42.160 --> 03:44.600
Her mother says.

03:44.600 --> 03:47.160
And it is your birthday.

03:47.520 --> 03:51.920
So, happy birthday, honey.

03:51.920 --> 03:55.320
Now, open that present.

03:55.320 --> 03:59.960
Her father says, it's from Evan.

03:59.960 --> 04:02.880
Hannah opens it.

04:02.880 --> 04:05.400
It's a helmet.

04:05.400 --> 04:07.280
Awesome.

04:07.280 --> 04:09.520
Hannah cries.

04:09.520 --> 04:14.600
But her older brother, Evan, laughs.

04:14.600 --> 04:19.200
You like watching skateboarding videos, I know.

04:19.200 --> 04:20.560
He says.

04:20.560 --> 04:25.440
But do you skateboard?

04:25.440 --> 04:27.600
Yes, I do.

04:27.600 --> 04:30.160
Hannah says hotly.

04:30.160 --> 04:34.920
Sometimes I'm Justin's skateboard.

04:34.920 --> 04:38.880
And I have my skateboard now.

04:38.880 --> 04:42.480
So I can do more.

04:42.480 --> 04:45.800
Can you jump or do tricks?

04:45.800 --> 04:47.880
Evan asks.

04:47.880 --> 04:51.920
Can you go fast and stay on?

04:51.920 --> 04:53.080
Duh.

04:53.080 --> 04:56.720
Hannah answers her brother angrily.

04:56.720 --> 05:00.280
What dumb questions?

05:00.280 --> 05:04.280
Evan, honey, please.

05:04.280 --> 05:06.320
Their mother says.

05:06.320 --> 05:09.960
It's Hannah's birthday.

05:09.960 --> 05:11.960
OK.

05:11.960 --> 05:15.440
Evan says.

05:15.440 --> 05:19.560
That weekend, Hannah takes her new skateboard

05:19.560 --> 05:23.840
to the skate park with Justin.

05:23.840 --> 05:26.720
There aren't many people there.

05:26.720 --> 05:30.680
Hannah is excited.

05:30.680 --> 05:31.720
OK.

05:31.720 --> 05:33.320
Let's go.

05:33.320 --> 05:39.960
Justin says, the two cousins begin skateboarding.

05:39.960 --> 05:43.720
Justin does a trick.

05:43.720 --> 05:48.320
Hannah skateboards up and down.

05:48.320 --> 05:51.560
Maybe I can jump now.

05:51.560 --> 05:53.760
She thinks.

05:53.760 --> 05:56.320
She goes faster.

05:56.320 --> 05:57.880
Then she jumps.

06:00.600 --> 06:05.640
But she falls off her skateboard.

06:05.640 --> 06:11.600
When Hannah is on the ground, somebody laughs.

06:11.600 --> 06:13.320
Oh, no.

06:13.320 --> 06:15.640
They're laughing at me.

06:15.640 --> 06:17.640
This is awful.

06:17.640 --> 06:20.160
She thinks.

06:20.160 --> 06:23.320
She gets up quickly.

06:23.320 --> 06:25.200
I'm going.

06:25.200 --> 06:27.320
She tells Justin.

06:27.320 --> 06:30.480
And she leaves.

06:30.480 --> 06:35.840
Just then, Owen arrives with his friends.

06:35.840 --> 06:42.280
They're laughing at a picture of Owen on his phone.

06:42.280 --> 06:46.160
But Hannah's far away now.

06:46.160 --> 06:49.360
No more skateboarding for me.

06:49.360 --> 06:50.840
She thinks.

06:50.840 --> 07:06.400
Chapter 3.

07:06.400 --> 07:08.120
First Steps.

07:08.120 --> 07:29.080
The next day, Justin stays at home with his family.

07:29.080 --> 07:33.320
But Hannah walks past the skate park.

07:33.320 --> 07:38.280
A lot of people are doing tricks.

07:38.280 --> 07:41.640
I can't skateboard there now.

07:41.640 --> 07:44.000
Hannah thinks.

07:44.000 --> 07:48.160
She watches Owen on his skateboard.

07:48.160 --> 07:53.520
He goes up in the air and comes down again.

07:53.520 --> 07:55.520
He's awesome.

07:55.520 --> 07:57.280
Hannah thinks.

07:57.280 --> 08:00.520
And I'm awful.

08:00.520 --> 08:03.760
She leaves the skate park and begins

08:03.760 --> 08:07.800
