08:29.520 --> 08:34.560
She is sitting on the grass with her baby boy.

08:34.560 --> 08:38.800
The little boy is trying to stand.

08:38.800 --> 08:43.760
Good boy, Michael.

08:43.760 --> 08:48.400
His mother says, stand up now.

08:48.400 --> 08:50.400
Yes.

08:50.400 --> 08:53.000
That's right.

08:53.000 --> 08:56.880
Michael stands up slowly.

08:56.880 --> 09:02.320
He takes one little step and falls down.

09:02.320 --> 09:06.320
Oh, come on now, Michael.

09:06.320 --> 09:10.680
His mother says, don't cry.

09:10.680 --> 09:13.720
Try again.

09:13.720 --> 09:18.480
Michael stops crying and laughs.

09:18.480 --> 09:23.360
He takes his mother's hand and stands up again.

09:23.360 --> 09:26.600
Good boy, Michael.

09:26.600 --> 09:32.760
His mother says, Michael sits down suddenly.

09:32.760 --> 09:39.760
He laughs and claps his hands happily.

09:39.760 --> 09:44.120
Hannah watches them for five minutes.

09:44.120 --> 09:52.720
Michael stands up and falls down again and again.

09:52.720 --> 09:55.880
Try again, Michael.

09:55.880 --> 10:04.720
His mother says, he doesn't stop falling, but it doesn't matter.

10:04.720 --> 10:06.680
Hannah thinks.

10:06.680 --> 10:18.160
He gets up and tries again, time after time, and he's no more than a baby.

10:18.160 --> 10:22.560
Hannah leaves the park and walks home.

10:22.560 --> 10:25.760
He thinks about baby Michael.

10:25.760 --> 10:27.760
Okay.

10:27.760 --> 10:32.600
She says, I need some more skateboard practice.

10:32.600 --> 10:50.720
But where can I go for that?

10:50.720 --> 10:57.720
Chapter four, practice, practice, practice.

10:57.720 --> 11:15.680
Hmm, let's see.

11:15.680 --> 11:18.360
The skate parks no good.

11:18.360 --> 11:20.160
Hannah thinks.

11:20.160 --> 11:25.000
I want to do my practice alone.

11:25.000 --> 11:29.440
That evening, she goes for a walk.

11:29.440 --> 11:34.840
Two blocks from her house, there's an office building.

11:34.840 --> 11:40.600
At half past five, everybody in it goes home.

11:40.600 --> 11:46.400
They drive all their cars out of the parking lot.

11:46.400 --> 11:53.080
Hey, I can skateboard here.

11:53.080 --> 11:56.280
Hannah thinks.

11:56.280 --> 12:03.240
The next evening, she takes her skateboard and helmet with her.

12:03.240 --> 12:07.040
I'm going out for some skateboard practice.

12:07.040 --> 12:14.280
She tells her mother, she skateboards to the parking lot.

12:14.280 --> 12:17.320
There are no cars there.

12:17.320 --> 12:22.160
First, she skateboards slowly.

12:22.160 --> 12:28.320
She is alone and nobody is watching.

12:28.320 --> 12:30.440
This is awesome.

12:30.440 --> 12:33.200
She thinks.

12:33.200 --> 12:38.680
After an hour, she goes home.

12:38.680 --> 12:41.800
She skateboards most evenings.

12:41.800 --> 12:47.240
Soon, she can go fast.

12:47.240 --> 12:51.760
One evening, she tries jumping.

12:51.760 --> 13:00.520
She skateboards across the parking lot and jumps.

13:00.520 --> 13:06.640
Suddenly, she is on the ground.

13:06.640 --> 13:11.680
A woman is going past on a bicycle.

13:11.680 --> 13:17.120
She sees Hannah on the ground and smiles at her.

13:17.120 --> 13:19.160
